Description: BasicEvents
        ===========
        
        python basic events send non-blocking
        
        Install
        -------
        
        pip install basicevents
        
        Example
        -------
        
        .. code:: python
        
            # recommeded check all examples
            from basicevents import subscribe, send
        
            @subscribe("pepito")
            def example(*args, **kwargs):
                print "recv signal, values:", args, kwargs
        
            def bla_bla():
                # much code
                # add to queue signals (non-blocking)
                send("pepito", 1, 2, 3, example="added queue")
                # create new thread for this request (non-blocking) not removing key instant
                send("pepito", 1, 2, 3, example="new thread", instant=True)
        
            bla_bla()
        
        Documentation functions
        -----------------------
        
        Only two functions!
        
        @subscribe() With this decorator you can subscribe to all events that
        are sent to
        
        send(, \*args, \*\*kwargs) If caught in a parameter called instant in
        kwargs with True call is placed in a new thread
        
        -  Note: Currently running as thread to allow sharing of memory, if you
           want an event to use more CPU (cores), you can run processes within
           the event.
        
        
        
